==English==
===Etymology===
from [[cube]] ... one story is in 1908 that as a new canvas by Braques was being carried past someone who said "Encore des Cubes! assez de cubisme!”.  The quotations below ascribe the coinage to Matisse.
===Noun===
# an art movement from the early 20th Century characterized by the depiction of flat geometrical planes
===Quotations===
* Matisse coined the name '''Cubism''' as a derisive joke. &mdash; ''The New Yorker'', 3 March 2003
* A few recall that, in 1908, he [Matisse] inspired the coinage of the term '''“cubism,”''' in disparagement of a movement that would eclipse his leading influence on the Parisian avant-garde. &mdash; ''The New Yorker'', 29 August 2005, page 78.